{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3500725,"name":"csos","username":"csos","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/58956e/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-03T16:22:19.051Z","cooked":"<p>Hi everyone,</p>
<p>Iâ€™m working with <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span> for swerve drive, and I want my robot to align precisely to a target using TX from Limelight. Since Iâ€™m new to <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span>, Iâ€™m looking for the best approach to achieve this. Should I use <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> for steering, or is there a better method?</p>
<p>For example I want the robot to move right and left based on the TX value without changing its rotation. How can I properly integrate Limelight data into <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span>â€™s drive commands? If youâ€™ve implemented something similar before, Iâ€™d love to hear your best practices!</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-02-03T16:22:19.051Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":232,"reads":309,"readers_count":308,"score":1231.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":484918,"topic_slug":"how-to-align-precisely-using-limelight-tx-with-yagsl","display_username":"csos","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":69234,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/how-to-align-precisely-using-limelight-tx-with-yagsl/484918/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3500733,"name":"","username":"nstrike","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nstrike/{size}/167038_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-03T16:27:43.674Z","cooked":"<p>I would use MegaTag2 and fuse that pose with <code>SwerveDrive.addVisionMeasurement</code> then do your aligning off of <code>SwerveDrive.getOdometryPose()</code></p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-02-03T16:27:43.674Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":297,"readers_count":296,"score":79.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":484918,"topic_slug":"how-to-align-precisely-using-limelight-tx-with-yagsl","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51887,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"YAGSL & YASS Creator "},"post_url":"/t/how-to-align-precisely-using-limelight-tx-with-yagsl/484918/2","custom_user_title":"YAGSL & YASS Creator ","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3500747,"name":"csos","username":"csos","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/58956e/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-03T16:45:44.073Z","cooked":"<p>I understand that after using <strong>MegaTag2</strong> and fusing the pose with <strong>SwerveDrive.addVisionMeasurement</strong>, I should align using <strong>SwerveDrive.getOdometryPose()</strong>.</p>
<p>But what exactly is the alignment command in this case? How do I perform the alignment after fusing the odometry with MegaTag2?</p>
<p>What Iâ€™m trying to do is this: Letâ€™s say the <strong>TX</strong> value is <strong>0</strong>. I want the robot to move left or right until the <strong>TX</strong> value reaches <strong>10</strong>. How can I achieve this in <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span>?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-02-03T16:45:44.073Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":277,"readers_count":276,"score":70.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":484918,"topic_slug":"how-to-align-precisely-using-limelight-tx-with-yagsl","display_username":"csos","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":51887,"username":"nstrike","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nstrike/{size}/167038_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":69234,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/how-to-align-precisely-using-limelight-tx-with-yagsl/484918/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3500819,"name":"Rylee L","username":"RyleeL","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ryleel/{size}/197248_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-03T18:01:33.355Z","cooked":"<p><a class="mention" href="/u/csos">@csos</a> what team are you on?</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"